# Trendzy Tours — Cursor AI Context

## Project
Travel agency website. Domain: trendzytours.com. Nagpur, India.
Nuxt 3.21.2 + TypeScript. Iteration 1 (public site) complete. Iteration 2 (dashboard) in progress.

## Stack
- Nuxt 3 + TypeScript + Vite
- Tailwind CSS 3 — gold/dark/cream palette; Playfair Display (headings), Inter (body)
- Pinia state: stores/auth.ts, stores/tours.ts, stores/ui.ts
- @nuxt/content — blog markdown in content/blog/
- @nuxt/image — use <NuxtImg> / <NuxtPicture>, not <img>
- @nuxt/icon + @heroicons/vue
- @headlessui/vue for accessible UI primitives
- vee-validate + zod — all forms use these two together
- jose — JWT auth, server-side only
- Brevo — email and newsletter
- @nuxtjs/sitemap (NOT @nuxtjs/seo — removed, incompatible with Nuxt 3.21)

## Folder Conventions
- pages/ → Nuxt file-based routing
- components/global/ → TheHeader, TheFooter, TheMobileMenu
- components/home/ → page section components
- components/tours/ → TourCard, TourGrid
- components/dashboard/ → DashHeader, DashSidebar
- components/ui/ → AppButton, AppBadge, AppSectionTitle (reuse these)
- composables/ → useContactForm, useNewsletterForm, useTours
- middleware/ → auth.ts (JWT guard), role.ts (RBAC: admin/sales/customer/seo)
- data/ → static seed data (no CMS)
- server/api/ → Nitro API routes

## Coding Rules
- Always use TypeScript with strict types
- Use <script setup lang="ts"> in all SFCs
- Use <NuxtImg> / <NuxtPicture> for all images — never raw <img>
- Use AppButton, AppBadge, AppSectionTitle from components/ui/ — don't recreate
- Mobile-first Tailwind classes (sm: md: lg:)
- Forms: vee-validate + zod schema, never manual validation
- Don't add @nuxtjs/seo or nuxt-og-image — they break Nuxt 3.21
- Dashboard pages must have definePageMeta({ middleware: ['auth', 'role'] })
- routeRules: prerender static, isr dynamic, ssr:false dashboard

## API Endpoints (already exist, don't duplicate)
- GET /api/tours — all tours
- GET /api/tours/[slug] — single tour
- POST /api/contact — contact form
- POST /api/newsletter — newsletter
- POST /api/auth/login | GET /api/auth/me | POST /api/auth/logout
